{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"rot-tarn-revel","description":"# S1 — Terraform base: EC2 box, networking, DNS subdomain, IAM, SSM secrets, state/backups\n\n## Why\nThe PoC needs one cost-conscious, reproducible AWS host for Gerrit + the rebar MCP.\nCodifying it as IaC is runtime-free and delivers the freeze-and-restore RTO (rebuild\nfrom Terraform) without adding cost — so it serves P3 (reusability) without touching\nP2 (cost). Everything else in this epic lands on this substrate.\n\n## What\n- New `infra/terraform/` using roll-your-own raw resources (the ec2-instance module\n  adds indirection at N=1):\n  - `t4g.large` (Graviton, ~8 GB) on Amazon Linux 2023 arm64; gp3 root + a separate\n    gp3 data volume mounted at `/var/gerrit`; IMDSv2 required.\n  - Default VPC; security group inbound 443 (HTTPS) + 29418 (Gerrit SSH); admin\n    access via SSM Session Manager (no inbound 22). One Elastic IP.\n  - Route 53 A record `rebar.solutions.navateam.com` -> EIP (parent zone already in\n    the account; this story creates the subdomain record).\n  - IAM instance role: SSM Parameter Store read (+ KMS decrypt), CloudWatch basic.\n  - SSM Parameter Store SecureString params (placeholders) for the Gerrit secrets,\n    the GitHub replication deploy key, the rebar MCP HMAC signing key, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY.\n  - Terraform S3 backend with `use_lockfile=true` (no DynamoDB); DLM daily EBS\n    snapshots of the data volume.\n- Packaging: ensure `infra/` is excluded from ALL distribution channels.\n\n## Scope\nIn: the TF base + DNS subdomain + IAM + SSM scaffolding + state/backup config + the\npackaging exclusion. Out: Gerrit/MCP containers (S2), Gerrit config (S3), replication\n(S5), GitHub lockdown (S6).\n\n## Files\n- `infra/terraform/*.tf` (new)\n- `pyproject.toml` (`[tool.hatch.build.targets.sdist]` include is `[\"src/rebar\",\"tests\",\"README.md\"]`\n  so `infra/` is excluded by default — add an explicit exclude + a build-artifact check to keep it that way)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `terraform -chdir=infra/terraform validate` and `plan` succeed; `apply` stands up a\n      reachable `t4g.large` with EIP, gp3 root + data volume mounted at `/var/gerrit`, IMDSv2 enforced.\n- [ ] `rebar.solutions.navateam.com` resolves (Route 53 A -> EIP); SG allows 443 + 29418;\n      admin access via SSM Session Manager with no inbound 22.\n- [ ] The instance role reads the SSM SecureString params; secrets are pulled at boot to a\n      `chmod 600` file (no plaintext secrets in user_data).\n- [ ] Terraform state lives in S3 with native lockfile; DLM creates daily snapshots of the data volume.\n- [ ] A built sdist AND wheel contain NO `infra/` files (verified against the built artifacts),\n      and the Homebrew / MCP-registry distribution likewise excludes `infra/`.","id":"5bfc-c3f8-72d6-40dc","parent_id":"d251-05e1-eb55-43b2","priority":2,"tags":["infra","aws","terraform"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"infra: S1 — Terraform base (EC2, networking, DNS subdomain, IAM, SSM secrets, state/backups)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782685470035347001,"uuid":"b355c849-bf93-4da3-a2d1-d48de17922c9"}